lw
===

Commandline Tool for Liquid Web API

<badge travis ingydotnet/lw>

= Synopsis

  lw help
  lw auth

  lw config username <your-lw-username>
  lw config password <your-lw-password>

  lw server-list
  lw server <id>
  lw server-create
  lw server-destroy

= Description

`lw` is a commandline tool for interacting with the Liquid Web public API. ie
Creating VM servers with your liquid web account, getting server information,
etc. See:

* https://www.liquidweb.com/
* https://www.stormondemand.com/api/docs/v1/

= Installation

The simplest way to install `lw` is:

  git clone https://github.com/ingydotnet/lw
  source $PWD/lw/init

Now the `lw` command is ready to use, including command completion and
manpages.

Add the `source …` line above to your shell's startup file to make it
persistent. The path to the `init` script must be an absolute path.

